px;line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Obviously, a confluence of issues prevents=
 Fetterman from
emerging out of the party=E2=80=99s ashes as a spokesman. His maverick auth=
enticity is double-edged: He=E2=80=99s not a party man. The Democratic base=
 views him with suspicion and still craves a hardy resistance movement, for=
 which he is very clearly not the guy. But <em>interest</em> in Fetterman, =
as an experiment in alternate models for the party, has undeniably grown si=
nce the election.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p =
style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">A source close to Schumer and
Jeffries pushed back on the notion that the party is in the market for a si=
ngular messenger. Instead, this person said, Democrats are banking on a <em=
>team</em> of warriors=E2=80=94akin to the leaderless #Resistance-fueled wa=
ve that retook the House in the 2018 midterms, or the cohort that withstood=
 an expected shellacking in 2022, post-<em>Dobbs</em>. They=E2=80=99re also=
 counting on Trump=E2=80=99s inevitable mismanagement of the government and=
 inability to lower inflation to drive voters back into their arms. =E2=80=
=9CIt=E2=80=99s
hard to be heard right now during the president=E2=80=99s next 100 days,=E2=
=80=9D the Democratic leadership source said. =E2=80=9CTrump is going to ge=
t his runway, but it=E2=80=99s not going to last long. He doesn=E2=80=99t s=
eem to be laser-focused on lowering costs or doing anything economically.=
=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D=
"margin:0;">Still, with so much noise around Trump, wouldn=E2=80=99t it be =
easier to break through with <em>one </em>messenger who appeals to the vote=
rs that Democrats lost? A former
D.N.C. operative told me that Fetterman=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Ccenter-left=E2=
=80=9D messaging stands a good chance of attracting independent voters. =E2=
=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s what appeals to most of the country, who don=E2=80=99t a=
ctually give a shit about politics, right?=E2=80=9D the operative said. =E2=
=80=9CFetterman=E2=80=99s not talking about stupid Bernie woke-left shit th=
at cost us the fucking election.=E2=80=9D</p></div>
